article.headline: Mizusawa leads Oregon to win
article.linkText: No. 24 Ducks goose Grizzlies on late jumper
article.story: EUGENE, Ore. (AP) -- Corrie Mizusawa's running jumper with 13.7 seconds gave Oregon (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today; No. 22 AP) a 53-52 victory over Montana on Friday night. Mizusawa took the ball off an inbounds pass and drove through the lane for the winner. The Grizzlies had a chance to win, but failed to score on two attempts in the final seconds. Mizusawa finished the game with 13 points to lead the Ducks (7-1). Andrea Bills had 10 points and set a career-high with 21 rebounds. Hollie Tyler had 21 points and 18 rebounds to pace Montana (5-2), which lost for the first time since falling to Texas on Nov. 30. Katie Edwards added 13 points. The teams traded scoring runs in the first half, and Montana led 28-25 at the break. Brandi Davis capped a 10-point Oregon run with a layup with 6:30 left in the first half. Montana responded with a nine-point run, highlighted by six from Tyler. Oregon won for the second time in three games without Cathrine Kraayeveld, who injured her right knee in practice Dec. 2.
